    <title type="text">Digital Corpus of Sanskrit</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a
      href="http://kjc-fs-cluster.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/dcs/index.php">DCS: Digital Corpus of
      Sanskrit</a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><img height="81"
      src="http://kjc-fs-cluster.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/dcs/img/TabBg.gif" width="200" />
      </blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span class="techfont">D<span
      style="font-size: x-small;">CS</span></span><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">, the <span class="techfont">D</span>igital <span
      class="techfont">C</span>orpus of <span class="techfont">S</span>anskrit,
      is a searchable collection of lemmatized Sanskrit texts. It offers free internet access to a
      part of the database of the linguistic program <span
      class="techfont">SanskritTagger</span>, which has been under constant development
      since 1999. </span>&nbsp;</blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"></span><div><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><a
      href="http://kjc-fs-cluster.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/dcs/index.php?contents=intro_sanskrit_tagger">Technical
      background</a> and <a
      href="http://kjc-fs-cluster.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/dcs/index.php?contents=intro_dcs_design">structure
      of the corpus</a></span></div><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span
      class="techfont">DCS</span> is designed for research in Sanskrit linguistics and
      philology. Users can search for lexical units and their collocations in a corpus of about
      3.250.000 manually tagged words in 430.000 sentences. In addition, <span
      class="techfont">DCS</span> generates distributional key values and performs
      statistical tests that can be used to assess the distribution of lexical units from a
      chronological perspective. The digital corpus offers two points of entry for the philological
      research: </span><br /><ol><li><span style="font-size: x-small;">
      Lexical units can be retrieved from the dictionary via a query interface or a dictionary page.
      For each lexical unit contained in the corpus, <span class="techfont">DCS</span>
      offers the complete set of references and a statistical evaluation based on historical
      principles. </span> <div><span style="font-size: x-small;"> More about the
      <a
      href="http://kjc-fs-cluster.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/dcs/index.php?contents=help_query">query
      interface</a>, the <a
      href="http://kjc-fs-cluster.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/dcs/index.php?contents=help_dictionary">dictionary</a>
      and the <a
      href="http://kjc-fs-cluster.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/dcs/index.php?contents=help_details">detail
      evaluation</a> of lexical units </span></div></li><li><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"> As an alternative, philological research can start from the
      interlinear lexical analysis that accompanies each text contained in the database.
      </span><div><span style="font-size: x-small;"> Information about the <a
      href="http://kjc-fs-cluster.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/dcs/index.php?contents=help_text">text
      interface</a></span> </div></li></ol><span style="font-size:
      x-small;">As a first step, it is recommended to use either the <a
      href="http://kjc-fs-cluster.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/dcs/index.php?contents=abfrage">query</a>
      or the <a
      href="http://kjc-fs-cluster.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/dcs/index.php?contents=dictionary">dictionary</a>
      page to search for lexical units or to have a look at the <a
      href="http://kjc-fs-cluster.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/dcs/index.php?contents=texte">text
      collection</a>. These pages can also be accessed using the main menu at the top of this
      page. The <a
      href="http://kjc-fs-cluster.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/dcs/index.php?contents=help_center">help
      center</a> gives a structured and detailed introduction in the functions of the <span
      class="techfont">DCS</span>.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span
      style="font-size: x-small;">Version 1.6., March 2012 - <a
